<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1164] kafka should depend on snappy 1.0.5 (instead of 1.0.4.1)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1164</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a bug in snappy 1.0.4.1, that makes it not work when using java 7, on MacOSX.  This issue is fixed in snappy 1.0.5.  We&apos;ve confirmed this locally.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ptaoussanis/carmine/issues/5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/ptaoussanis/carmine/issues/5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, the kafka distribution should update the KafkaProject.scala file to call out version 1.0.5 instead of 1.0.4.1.  I believe this file is used when generating the pom.xml file for kafka.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
